      "format": "docx",
      "paragraphs": [
        "INSULATION",
        "Scope:",
        "The scope of work comprises the supply, installation, testing & commissioning & document of Insulation along with its accessories for M/s Zydus Animal Health and Investments Ltd.  The specifications shall be read in conjunction with bill of quantities.",
        "Objective:",
        "The purpose of this document is to specify the requirements of Hot & Cold Insulation and to covers information about its accessories.",
        "Specification",
        "Description:",
        "The scope of work covers thermal insulation for:",
        "i)\tCold Insulation 1) \t Pipes",
        "2)          Ducts",
        "3)          Equipment\u2019s",
        "ii)\tHot Insulation\t  1)\t Pipes",
        "2)          Ducts",
        "3)          Equipment\u2019s",
        "4)          Exhaust flues (if any)",
        "Material:",
        "Following materials shall be used:",
        "i)  Cold Insulation\t1)Fire inhibiting expanded polystyrene rigid section 18kg/cum thermal conductivity of not more than 0.03 w/m \u1d52C at 10 deg C mean temperature. (Not applicable)",
        "2) Duct - Elastomeric sheet of class \u201cO\u201d self-extinguishing CFC free with a thermal conductivity of not more than 0.035 w/m\u1d52K at 0\u1d52C and suitable for a service temperature of - 40 \u1d52C to 105 C. The density of rubber shall be minimum 60 kg/M\u00b3 and water vapour diffusion resistance should not be more than 4000. The material should be CFC free and UV resistant.",
        "Piping - Elastomeric sheet / tubing (Nitrile Rubber) of class \u201cO\u201d self-extinguishing CFC free with a thermal conductivity of not more than 0.035 w/m\u1d52K at 0\u1d52C and suitable for a service temperature of - 40 \u1d52C to 105 C with factory installed glass cloth.",
        "3)  Close cell cross- linked Polyethylene Foam sheet of Class \u201cO\u201d fire rating as per DIN 4102 with factory baked Aluminium foil faced, self-extinguishing with a thermal conductivity of not more than 0.032 w/m\u1d52K at 0\u1d52C and density shall be 30+/- 10% as per DIN 53420 .",
        "4) Resin bonded fiberglass having K value not more than 0.032 and density not less than 24 kg/cu. m. (Not applicable)",
        "ii)  Hot Insulation\t1) Elastomeric tubing (Nitrile rubber) of class \u201cO\u201d                                                        self-extinguishing CFC free with a thermal conductivity of not more than 0.03 w/m\u1d52K at 0 \u1d52C and suitable for service temperature of -40 \u1d52C to 105 \u1d52C.",
        "2) Resin bonded rock wool confirming to ASTM C592 class II for blanket and ASTM C547 class III for preformed pipe section having density more than 96 kg/m3 and thermal conductivity not more than 0.05 mW/cm\u00b0C at 100 deg C mean temperature and with one side wire netting of size 24G x 20. The material shall be suitable for intended operational temperature range from ambient to 550\u00b0C (Only for hot water) (Not applicable)",
        "Duct Insulation:",
        "Duct located INDOOR / OUTDOOR spaces shall be insulated to the following thickness.",
        "** Thickness mentioned in BOQ shall be treated as Final **",
        "Indoor insulation shall be applied as follows (For EPS):",
        "Clean the duct surface & apply a coat of bituminous paint. Apply hot bitumen 80/25 @ 1.5 kg/sqm    on the surface and the inner side of insulation material.",
        "Stick insulation slabs & hold at 1000mm centre with PVC Strapping & blind the surface with hot bitumen at 1.5 kg/sq. m. Seal the joints with approved sealant or hot bitumen.",
        "Wrap 10 mil glass cloths with PVC strapping at 1000mm spacing & seal with hot bitumen / Aluminium foil of 42 Gauge with 50 mm overlap and seal all joints using BOPP tape of Wonder / 3M make.",
        "Indoor insulation shall be applied as follows (For Nitrile / Polyethylene):",
        "Clean the duct surface thoroughly & apply a coat of  adhesive recommended by the manufacturer on the duct as well as on sheet and allow it to cure (Self-adhesive sheet can also be used )",
        "Stick insulation slabs with pre-laminated aluminium foil of minimum 30 micron on duct uniformly. Seal the joints with approved self-adhesive Aluminium tape of same material.",
        "Flanges or any other exposed portion should be covered with 50 mm wide insulation slab of same material having same thickness.",
        "Outdoor insulation shall be applied as follows (For EPS):",
        "Clean the duct surface & apply a coat of bituminous paint. Apply hot bitumen 80/25 @ 1.5 kg/sqm on the surface and the inner side of insulation material.",
        "Stick insulation slabs & hold at 1000mm centre with 24G galvanized steel wire or PVC strapping & blind the surface with hot bitumen at 1.5 kg/sqm. Seal the joints with approved sealant.",
        "Wrap 10 mil glass cloth / 500 micron polythene sheet & seal with hot bitumen.",
        "Clad the duct with 0.5mm thick Al sheet with 50mm overlap and fixed with self-tapping no. 8 sheet metal screw and seal with mastic sealant.",
        "Outdoor insulation shall be applied as follows (For Nitrile/ Polyethylene):",
        "Clean the duct surface thoroughly & apply a coat of adhesive recommended by the manufacturer on the duct as well as on sheet and allow it to cure. (Self-adhesive sheet can also be used)",
        "Stick insulation slabs with/ without pre-laminated aluminium foil (as specified in BOQ) on duct uniformly. Seal the joints with approved self-adhesive Aluminium tape.",
        "Flanges or any other exposed portion should be covered with 50 mm wide insulation slab of same material and thickness.",
        "If insulation slab is without Aluminium foil then clad the duct with 0.5mm thick Al sheet with 50mm overlap and fixed with self-tapping no. 8 sheet metal screw and seal with mastic sealant.",
        "Pipe Insulation",
        "i) Cold Insulation",
        "Cold pipe insulation shall be selected as follows:",
        "Indoor Insulation (For EPS):",
        "Clean the duct surface & apply a coat of bituminous paint. Apply hot bitumen 80/25 @ 1.5 kg/sq. m on the surface and the inner side of insulation material."
      ],
